This file contains modifications from the original source code.

Original Project: stroop-simon-german (DiLi-Lab)
Source URL: https://github.com/DiLi-Lab/stroop-simon-german

The original stroop-simon-german project does not include a LICENSE file.

This implementation is based on the following paradigms:
- Stroop task: Stroop, J. R. (1935). Studies of interference in serial verbal reactions.
- Flanker task: Eriksen, B. A., & Eriksen, C. W. (1974). Effects of noise letters upon identification of a target letter in a nonsearch task.

Modifications made to the original code:

1. Framework Configuration
   - Added YAML-based configuration system (config.yaml, experiment.yaml)
   - Added command-line argument parsing (--participant_folder)

2. Task Changes
   - Changed from separate Stroop + Simon to combined Stroop + Flanker task
   - Made language configurable via YAML instead of German-only

3. Data Output
   - Modified output path structure: data/{participant_folder}/Stroop-Flanker/
   - Changed to CSV format for results

4. Code Structure
   - Converted from PsychoPy Builder output to standalone script
   - Added proper argument parsing and configuration loading

